{{Infobox person | name = Shashibhusan Dasgupta, Shashi Bhushan Dasgupta | birth_date = 1911 | birth_place = [[Chandrahar]], [[Bengal Presidency]] | death_date = 21 July 1964 | death_place = [[Kolkata]], [[West Bengal]], [[India]] | occupation = Scholar in philosophy, languages and literature, literary critic, author, theologian }}
'''Shashibhusan Dasgupta''', or '''Shashi Bhushan Dasgupta''', '''Shashibhusan''' and '''Shashi Bhusan Das Gupta''' (1911–1964) was a [[Bengali people|Bengali]] scholar of philosophy, languages, literature (particularly Bengali literature), literary critic, author and theologian.<ref>[http://sbufind.library.stonybrook.edu/vufind/Author/Home?author=Dasgupta%2C%20Shashi%20Bhushan%2C%201912-1964 "Shashi Bhushan Dasgupta"]. Stonybrook.edu.</ref>
Dasgupta was born in [[Chandrahar]] Village in modern [[Barisal Division]], South-Central Bangladesh. He obtained his IA from [[B M College]], Barisal, his BA (Hons) in Philosophy from [[Scottish Church College]], [[Kolkata]], [[West Bengal]], [[India]]. His MA in [[Bengali language|Bengali]] Language and Literature was from [[Calcutta University]] in 1935, and he subsequently joined Calcutta University's Bengali Department as a Researcher. Winning the 1937 [[Premchand Roychand]] Studentship due to his scholarship contributions, Dasgupta was appointed in Bengali Department a lecturer, and received his PhD in that department in 1939.
Dasgupta's chief opus is the identification of Indian spiritual meditation forms and demonstration of their relationship to [[Vajrayana|Tantric]] [[Buddhism]], to [[Saivite]], [[Sakta]] and [[Vaishnava]] religious philosophies, and to Bengali literature. He won the 1961 [[Sahitya Akademi Award]] for his work "[[Bharater Shakti-Sadhana O Shakta Sahitya]]."
Dasgupta had authored novels, plays, poems and children's books.<ref>{{cite web|author=Prof. Sirajul Islam |url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Dasgupta,_Shashibhusan |title=Mahbubul Haque, Banglapedia, National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh |publisher=Banglapedia.org |date=1964-07-21 |accessdate=2011-10-14}}</ref> Some editions of his works are published posthumously or in recently updated versions, and their exact or cited titles in English depend on the language variants being transliterated.
